physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Numerous skin-colored firm and non-pendunculated verrucous papules (0.5-1 cm in diameter) covering dorsal region of hands, wrists, ankles, dorsal aspects of shins and calves. Thick, hyperpigmented, and velvety skin in axillae and groin. Thickened and rough palms and soles. Tripe palms noted.
